        <h1>Christmas parade massacre suspect feels ‚Äòdemonized‚Äô following attack</h1>

                <time class="op-published" datetime="2021-12-02T01:47:17+00:00">2 Dec, 2021 01:47</time>
            </header>

    
    
    <p><strong>The suspect behind last month‚Äôs Waukesha Christmas parade massacre, which killed six people and injured 62 more, has claimed he feels ‚Äúdehumanized‚Äù and ‚Äúdemonized‚Äù in the aftermath of the attack.</strong></p>
    <p>39-year-old Darrell Brooks Jr. &ndash; a registered sex offender with a lengthy history of arrests &ndash; has been in jail for ten days as the chief suspect behind the deadly November attack. Speaking to Fox News on Wednesday, he said he feels <em>&ldquo;dehumanized&rdquo;</em> by the coverage of the case.</p>
<p><em>&ldquo;I just feel like I'm being monster &ndash; demonized,&rdquo;</em> Brooks told two Fox News reporters, who were reportedly the first visitors he had received in jail since his arrest.</p>
        
    <ul class="op-related-articles" title="Read more">
        <li><a href="https://www.rt.com/usa/541581-cnn-car-waukesha-christmas-parade/"></a></li>
    </ul>


<p>He also told the news network that even his mother had not visited since he allegedly drove his car into a crowd of Christmas parade attendees in Waukesha, Wisconsin on November 21.</p>
<p>Brooks&rsquo; mother, Dawn Woods, blamed a lack of mental health resources for the attack in a letter on Wednesday, claiming her son <em>&ldquo;was not given the help and resources he needed.&rdquo;</em></p>
<p>Brooks has an extensive criminal record and had been arrested less than a month before the attack for punching and running over a woman with the same car that was used to hit the parade attendees. He was released on a $1,000 bond not long before the parade attack.</p>
<p>Brooks has been charged with six counts of first-degree murder and is being held on a $5 million bail.</p>

