        <h1>'Ku Klux Klan' caucus accused of targeting Ilhan Omar</h1>

                <time class="op-published" datetime="2021-12-01T17:08:18+00:00">1 Dec, 2021 17:08</time>
        <time class="op-modified" dateTime="2021-12-01T17:20:51+00:00">1 Dec, 2021 17:20</time>    </header>

    
    
    <p><strong>Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (D-New York) has accused Republicans of having a ‚ÄúKu Klux Klan caucus‚Äù that is targeting Rep. Ilhan Omar (D-Minnesota) and others with racist attacks.</strong></p>
    <p>The spat between Omar and Rep. Lauren Boebert (R-Colorado) intensified this week as the former held a press conference and played an audio recording of a graphic phone call threatening violence against her. Omar used the call to urge action against Boebert for recent comments, including referring to her as a member of the <em>&ldquo;Jihad Squad.&rdquo;</em></p>
<p>On the voice message, a man calls Omar multiple slurs, appears to threaten her life, and accuses her of being a terrorist.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Listen to the phone call below (warning: graphic language):</p>
            <figure class="op-interactive">
            <iframe>
                <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Rep. Ilhan Omar (D-MN) plays a horrific death threat she received following Rep. Lauren Boebert‚Äôs (R-CO) recent Islamophobic attacks on her.<br><br>Warning: It&#39;s incredibly graphic. <a href="https://t.co/5PGODcaJOu">pic.twitter.com/5PGODcaJOu</a></p>&mdash; The Recount (@therecount) <a href="https://twitter.com/therecount/status/1465830674317914115?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">November 30, 2021</a></blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
            </iframe>
        </figure>
    

<p>Ocasio-Cortez came to the defense of her fellow &lsquo;Squad&rsquo; member on Wednesday, with a tweet accusing Rep. Kevin McCarthy (R-California) of leading a &ldquo;Ku Klux Klan caucus&rdquo; in an effort to take back control of the House from Democrats.</p>
<p><em>&ldquo;Kevin McCarthy is so desperate to be speaker that he is working with his Ku Klux Klan caucus to look aside and allow violent targeting of woc [women of color] members of Congress,&rdquo;</em> she tweeted, adding that these threats should not be ignored.&nbsp;</p>
            <figure class="op-interactive">
            <iframe>
                <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-cards="hidden"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">People truly don‚Äôt understand the scale, intensity, &amp; volume of threats targeting <a href="https://twitter.com/IlhanMN?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@IlhanMN</a>.<br><br>Kevin McCarthy is so desperate to be speaker that he is working with his Ku Klux Klan caucus to look aside &amp; allow violent targeting of woc members of Congress.<br><br>This cannot be ignored. <a href="https://t.co/ppridf6bZl">https://t.co/ppridf6bZl</a></p>&mdash; Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (@AOC) <a href="https://twitter.com/AOC/status/1466058094304239618?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">December 1, 2021</a></blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
            </iframe>
        </figure>
    

<p>The feud between Boebert and Omar began after a clip of Boebert went viral in which she mocked Omar as a potential terrorist. A later phone call between the two ended with Omar hanging up on Boebert.&nbsp;</p>
<p>On Friday, Boebert issued an apology to anyone in the <em>&ldquo;Muslim community&rdquo;</em> that she offended.&nbsp;</p>
            <figure class="op-interactive">
            <iframe>
                <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">I apologize to anyone in the Muslim community I offended with my comment about Rep. Omar. I have reached out to her office to speak with her directly. There are plenty of policy differences to focus on without this unnecessary distraction.</p>&mdash; Rep. Lauren Boebert (@RepBoebert) <a href="https://twitter.com/RepBoebert/status/1464289590282498050?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">November 26, 2021</a></blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
            </iframe>
        </figure>
    

<p>Omar has not directly responded to Boebert&rsquo;s tweet, but has called on Republican leadership to take action against the <em>&ldquo;hateful rhetoric&rdquo;</em> from the Colorado congresswoman.&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>&ldquo;This kind of hateful rhetoric and actions cannot go without punishment. There has to be accountability,&rdquo;</em> Omar said on Tuesday, adding that <em>&ldquo;if and when&rdquo;</em> Republicans fail to take action, <em>&ldquo;it&rsquo;s going to be our job to do that.&rdquo;</em></p>

